ControlPropertyState.AutoRuleBindingString: /*Email must have a subject and recipients to be sent*/If(Len(Trim(TextEmailSubject2.Text)) > 0 && !IsEmpty(MyPeople), DisplayMode.Edit, DisplayMode.Disabled)

/*Create semicolon separated list of people to email, send the email, reset subject & message fields*/           Set(_emailRecipientString, Concat(MyPeople, Mail & ";"));           Office365Outlook.SendEmail(_emailRecipientString, TextEmailSubject2.Text, TextEmailMessage2.Text, {Importance:"Normal"});           Reset(TextEmailSubject2);           Reset(TextEmailMessage2);           Clear(MyPeople)
